---
import { Icon } from "astro-icon/components";
---

<style>
  /* Smooth accordion animations */
  details {
    overflow: hidden;
    transition: all 0.3s cubic-bezier(0.87, 0, 0.13, 1);
  }

  details summary {
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }

  details[open] summary {
    border-bottom-left-radius: 0;
    border-bottom-right-radius: 0;
  }

  details .content {
    overflow: hidden;
    max-height: 0;
    transition: max-height 0.3s cubic-bezier(0.87, 0, 0.13, 1);
  }

  details[open] .content {
    max-height: 1000px; /* Large enough value for content */
  }

  details summary::-webkit-details-marker {
    display: none;
  }

  details summary::marker {
    display: none;
  }
</style>

<div class="space-y-0">
  <details
    class="group overflow-hidden rounded-t-3xl border border-stone-400 bg-stone-100"
  >
    <summary
      class="group -mb-px flex w-full cursor-pointer items-center justify-between rounded-t-3xl border-stone-400 bg-stone-100 p-4 text-left transition-colors hover:bg-stone-200"
    >
      <span class="text-lg font-bold">Who are we?</span>
      <Icon
        name="ph:caret-down"
        class="ease-[cubic-bezier(0.87,0,0.13,1)] h-5 w-5 font-bold text-stone-600 transition-transform duration-300 group-open:rotate-180"
      />
    </summary>
    <div
      class="content -mb-px overflow-hidden border-t border-stone-400 bg-white"
    >
      <div class="p-4">
        We're a University of Waterloo student design team, made up of students
        with backgrounds in Chemistry, Computation, Instrumentation, and
        Business. We all share a common passion for innovation and advancing the
        field of nanotechnology!
      </div>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details class="group overflow-hidden border border-stone-400 bg-stone-100">
    <summary
      class="group -mb-px flex w-full cursor-pointer items-center justify-between border-stone-400 bg-stone-100 p-4 text-left transition-colors hover:bg-stone-200"
    >
      <span class="text-lg font-bold">What do we do?</span>
      <Icon
        name="ph:caret-down"
        class="ease-[cubic-bezier(0.87,0,0.13,1)] h-5 w-5 font-bold text-stone-600 transition-transform duration-300 group-open:rotate-180"
      />
    </summary>
    <div
      class="content -mb-px overflow-hidden border-t border-stone-400 bg-white"
    >
      <div class="p-4">
        Our team is working on building a nanocar, a molecular machine with
        applications in science, healthcare and engineering, optimized for
        speed, functionality and performance to compete in the next
        International Nanocar Race.
      </div>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details class="group overflow-hidden border border-stone-400 bg-stone-100">
    <summary
      class="group -mb-px flex w-full cursor-pointer items-center justify-between border-stone-400 bg-stone-100 p-4 text-left transition-colors hover:bg-stone-200"
    >
      <span class="text-lg font-bold">When can I join?</span>
      <Icon
        name="ph:caret-down"
        class="ease-[cubic-bezier(0.87,0,0.13,1)] h-5 w-5 font-bold text-stone-600 transition-transform duration-300 group-open:rotate-180"
      />
    </summary>
    <div
      class="content -mb-px overflow-hidden border-t border-stone-400 bg-white"
    >
      <div class="p-4">
        Research and development is continuous throughout the year, and new
        members are welcome to join anytime! We always look forward to adding
        diverse skills to our ongoing projects!
      </div>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details class="group overflow-hidden border border-stone-400 bg-stone-100">
    <summary
      class="group -mb-px flex w-full cursor-pointer items-center justify-between border-stone-400 bg-stone-100 p-4 text-left transition-colors hover:bg-stone-200"
    >
      <span class="text-lg font-bold"
        >I don't have a lot of experience, should I still apply?</span
      >
      <Icon
        name="ph:caret-down"
        class="ease-[cubic-bezier(0.87,0,0.13,1)] h-5 w-5 font-bold text-stone-600 transition-transform duration-300 group-open:rotate-180"
      />
    </summary>
    <div
      class="content -mb-px overflow-hidden border-t border-stone-400 bg-white"
    >
      <div class="p-4">
        You don't need extensive experience to join our team! While some
        knowledge is beneficial, it isn't necessary. What matters most is a
        strong desire to innovate and a readiness to explore the future of
        nanotechnology. If you're enthusiastic about getting involved and eager
        to learn, we'd love to have you!
        <p class="mt-4">
          You'll be surrounded by students with diverse knowledge who are ready
          to provide mentorship and support!
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details class="group overflow-hidden border border-stone-400 bg-stone-100">
    <summary
      class="group -mb-px flex w-full cursor-pointer items-center justify-between border-stone-400 bg-stone-100 p-4 text-left transition-colors hover:bg-stone-200"
    >
      <span class="text-lg font-bold"
        >What is the expected time commitment for team members?</span
      >
      <Icon
        name="ph:caret-down"
        class="ease-[cubic-bezier(0.87,0,0.13,1)] h-5 w-5 font-bold text-stone-600 transition-transform duration-300 group-open:rotate-180"
      />
    </summary>
    <div
      class="content -mb-px overflow-hidden border-t border-stone-400 bg-white"
    >
      <div class="p-4">
        The anticipated time commitment varies based on your availability and
        project needs. We are students too and are always flexible to
        accommodate your schedule.
        <p class="mt-4">
          Keep in mind that, the more you put into this experience, the more
          you'll get out of it! More time put into this can lead to more
          opportunities for engagement and growth :)
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details class="group overflow-hidden border border-stone-400 bg-stone-100">
    <summary
      class="group -mb-px flex w-full cursor-pointer items-center justify-between border-stone-400 bg-stone-100 p-4 text-left transition-colors hover:bg-stone-200"
    >
      <span class="text-lg font-bold"
        >Can I be a part of Formula Nano while on a work term?</span
      >
      <Icon
        name="ph:caret-down"
        class="ease-[cubic-bezier(0.87,0,0.13,1)] h-5 w-5 font-bold text-stone-600 transition-transform duration-300 group-open:rotate-180"
      />
    </summary>
    <div
      class="content -mb-px overflow-hidden border-t border-stone-400 bg-white"
    >
      <div class="p-4">
        Of course! We accept students on both study and work terms. While our
        main lab facilities are located on campus at the University of Waterloo
        for hands-on research, team members also work remotely from all over the
        world. This flexibility allows you to join regardless of your location!
      </div>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details class="group overflow-hidden border border-stone-400 bg-stone-100">
    <summary
      class="group -mb-px flex w-full cursor-pointer items-center justify-between border-stone-400 bg-stone-100 p-4 text-left transition-colors hover:bg-stone-200"
    >
      <span class="text-lg font-bold">What can I do as a new team member?</span>
      <Icon
        name="ph:caret-down"
        class="ease-[cubic-bezier(0.87,0,0.13,1)] h-5 w-5 font-bold text-stone-600 transition-transform duration-300 group-open:rotate-180"
      />
    </summary>
    <div
      class="content -mb-px overflow-hidden border-t border-stone-400 bg-white"
    >
      <div class="p-4">
        As a new team member at Formula Nano, depending on our current project
        stage and your own preferences, you can contribute in numerous ways,
        including:
        <ul class="mt-2 list-inside list-disc">
          <li>
            Hands-on Research: Assist with lab experiments and ongoing projects.
          </li>
          <li>
            Collaboration: Join discussions and brainstorming sessions, bringing
            your unique perspective to our research.
          </li>
          <li>
            Project Support: Help with data analysis, literature reviews, and
            documentation.
          </li>
          <li>
            Design and Simulation: Contribute to the design of simulation
            components or experimental setups for hands-on experience.
          </li>
          <li>
            Skill Development: Gain exposure to new techniques and tools
            relevant to nanotechnology.
          </li>
          <li>
            Business Development and Outreach: Support sponserships, finances,
            and promote our research and team via social media.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details
    class="group overflow-hidden rounded-b-3xl border border-stone-400 bg-stone-100"
  >
    <summary
      class="group -mb-px flex w-full cursor-pointer items-center justify-between rounded-b-3xl border-stone-400 bg-stone-100 p-4 text-left transition-colors hover:bg-stone-200"
    >
      <span class="text-lg font-bold"
        >What's the process for joining Formula Nano?</span
      >
      <Icon
        name="ph:caret-down"
        class="ease-[cubic-bezier(0.87,0,0.13,1)] h-5 w-5 font-bold text-stone-600 transition-transform duration-300 group-open:rotate-180"
      />
    </summary>
    <div
      class="content -mb-px overflow-hidden rounded-b-3xl border-t border-stone-400 bg-white"
    >
      <div class="p-4">
        <ol class="mt-2 list-inside list-decimal space-y-2">
          <li>
            Submit Your Application <br />Start by filling out our recruitment
            form to tell us a bit about yourself and why you're interested in
            Formula Nano. If we think you'd be a great fit, we'll reach out to
            schedule a casual chat!
          </li>
          <li>
            Casual Interview <br />You'll have a laid-back conversation with a
            few of our members. This is a perfect time to ask questions and get
            to know Formula Nano better! We'll also ask a few role-specific
            questions to see how your skills match up with our current projects
            :)
            <p class="mt-4">
              In the meantime, check out our social media to see what we're
              working on!
            </p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </div>
  </details>
</div>
